The independent schools of Scotland benefit from a curriculum of academic excellence, with this trend continued in 2018 with another set of exceptional results in the exams, reinforced by individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other community initiatives.
With more than 30,000 students throughout Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (CIS), are striving to achieve the best level of service for both students and parents.
Independent schools intend to prepare their students for further education and access to universities, as well as for the career they have chosen and to take their place as global citizens.
Since this is an educational sector capable of designing and implementing a tailored school curriculum, we see that modern languages continue to be a popular and sought-after theme in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "If we speak to a man in a language he understands, we can enter his mind.
If we speak to him in his own language, we can enter his heart."
This quote reminds us well that we cannot only rely on English when we want to create relationships and trust with people from other countries.
Based on the results of the recent exams this year, we find that the languages are at the top of the tables, with the highest utilization rates of independent schools.
A total of 68% of students studying foreign languages reached the maximum classification of A.
