The study, carried out by scientists from the National Trust for Scotland, will follow common and fruit bats as well as long ears browns and Daubenton bats in the Inverewe Gardens in Wester Ross.
Special recorders will be placed in key locations scattered by the property to follow the activities of the bats along the station.
Mobile studies will also be carried out by NTS staff and volunteers with portable detectors.
