The populations of bats in Scotland and throughout the United Kingdom have declined considerably over the past century.
These animals are threatened by construction and development works that affect the dorms and make habitat scarce.
Wind turbines and lightnings are also a threat, together with the kill papers and some chemical treatments of building materials, in addition to the attacks of domestic cats.
In fact, bats are not blind.
