2004: On 26 December a strong earthquake on the west coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh in northern Sumatra originated a tsunami that reached 14 countries, killing 226,000 people along the Indian Ocean coast, more than half of which in Aceh.
2005: A series of seismos reached the western coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
