2010: A magnitude 7.5 earthquake hit one of the Mentawai islands off Sumatra, triggering a tsunami with waves of up to 10 metres that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
2016: A shallow earthquake struck the Pidie Jaya region in Aceh, spreading the destruction and panic among people who remembered the devastation caused by the deadly earthquake and tsunami of 2004.
